snippet.textDisplay:
This theory that the next guy always needs to be paid more than previous guy makes absolutely no sense. In no way should Dak be compared to Mahomes. Dak let's say is one tier below the Mahomes aka elite tier. His pay should be commensurate to how good he actually is. Taking that into account it should be simple to adjust for the rate of inflation from prior years just how a raise in any other type of job marketplace to maintain the same standards of living. One can be so generic and use the standard 3-5% and it still be fair where avg workers receive typically a 2.5-3%increase and top employees are closer to the 4-5% range. Now if he grows and plays way better he can demand even more just like anyone else who excels in their respective fields. Dak is a good QB but no way hes worth 40mill nor should compared to the likes of Mahomes, Brees, or Wilson . ex. If 30 mill was the pay for the player similar Dak last year he should be offered 31.5mill which is a 5% raise, it should be that easy to do.


Dak is ranked 11th as QB the others Ranked 8-12 are all being paid between (M. Safford) 27 and 33 mill (A. Rodgers) a year. even using those numbers he would fall at 34.5mill if we somehow agree Dak is as good or better than Rodgers, which not many would argue.

It just seems insane for any business to operate on the idea that ones pay must be more than the prior employee just because that person has secured a respective role. Quality and abilities should be the determining factor more than I deserve more just because Joe Player signed half a season ago for X price. Sooner or later the market itself for the players will either implode or continue to skyrocket at a rate the teams cannot sustain without it hurting the pockets of the most important people which is the fans.
